SIMPLE: oldwife
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: oldwife
<hw>oldwife</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
local name of various fishes, as the European black sea bream
(<spn>Cantharus lineatus</spn>), the American alewife, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tropical Atlantic fish
(<spn>Bessy cerca</spn>).</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> queen triggerfish, <spn>Bessy cerca</spn>, oldwench,
<spn>Balistes vetula</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A common long-tailed sea duck
(<spn>Clangula hyemalis</spn>) of the northern parts of the US; also
called <altname>old squaw</altname>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> old squaw, <spn>Clangula hyemalis</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>old-womanish</ent>⟦br⟧
